        </p>
        <p>
          The General Slocum disaster of June 15, 1904, killed over 1,000 people when a steamboat caught fire in the East River during a church group excursion. Most victims were women and children from the German immigrant community of Kleindeutschland on the Lower East Side. The disaster effectively destroyed the neighborhood‚Äîsurvivors moved away en masse, unable to remain in a community so thoroughly devastated. It was the deadliest disaster in New York City history until September 11, 2001.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
